oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: World War I discharge certificate for Kenneth G. Redford
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This certificate shows the honorable discharge for Musician Kenneth G. Redford, HQ Co., 114 FA, 30th Div. The certificate gives a physical description and enlistment record and was filed with the Williamson County Register of Deeds to certify his service. Redford was from Franklin, Williamson County, Tennessee. Discharged military personnel were required by state law to register with their respective regster of deeds.
